metadata.name: The carrelet
metadata.description:
The "carrelets" are built mainly in the second half of the 20th century on the banks of the Saint-Estèphe estuary, France. To this day, some fishermen in the area continue to use them as fishing huts.

For this shot I spent weeks studying hanging meteorology to find the perfect day and light to do this long exposure where the reference point is centered with the sky for added visual impact.

Artist name: Adrià Lleixà Bel
Edition 1/1
Date Captured: 04/02/2016
Location: Saint-Estèphe, France
